        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 4:54PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 453 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Morgan Springs, or 12 miles west of Waldron, moving northeast at 60
mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cauthron...                       Oliver...
Echo...                           Hon...
Winfield...                       Morgan Springs...
Lucas...                          Bates...
Liberty...                        Booneville...
Barber...                         Sugar Grove...
Carolan...                        Grayson...
Elm Park...                       Glendale in Logan County...
Ione...                           Waldron...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
western Arkansas.</instruction>
